Genitalia: spermathecae paired, slightly fused at their base; receptacles slender throughout their length and slightly bent laterally (
Fig. 30H
).

Urticating setae: lacking (
Fig. 30E
).

Colour pattern: in ethanol the colour is brown; with carapace, legs, and palps darker; chelicerae reddish. In live specimens the colour is dark brown with the femora slightly darker (
Fig. 1K
).

Eyes: anterior eye row procurved, posterior eye row straight. Periocular pigmentation absent. AME and PLE as integumentary spots, ALE and PME reduced. Eye sizes and interocular distances: AME 0.06; ALE 0.12; PME 0.06; PLE 0.08; AME–AME 0.12; AME–ALE 0.08; PME–PME 0.36; PME–PLE 0.02; ALE–PLE 0.02. Ocular tubercle undeveloped, width 0.8; length 0.24; clypeus lacking (
Fig. 31D
). Labium: length 0.625; width 1.0; with 17 cuspules. Maxilla inner corner with approximately 77 cuspules (
Fig. 31E
). Cheliceral promargin with 11 teeth (proximal to distal: firstsecond large, third small, fourth medium, fifth small, sixth-seventh medium, eighth-tenth large, eleventh small). Sternum length 2.07. Sigillae circular, second, third, and fourth pairs hardly visible; fourth pair once its length from the margin (
Fig. 31C, F
).

Tibia I with two apophyses, which do not originate from a common base, Pap very reduced with one large spinose seta on ventral face, spinose seta very long and almost replaces the Pap; Rap reduced with one very large spinose seta on prolateral face, spinose seta almost replaces the Rap (
Fig. 31G, H
). Metatarsus I straight (
Fig. 31I
).

