Palp: embolus as wide as tegulum at the base, tapering distally and larger than tegulum; 
SA
retrolaterally extended, ends before the embolus base (
Fig. 32C
). 
SA
does not curve in posterior; VG shallow (
Fig. 32D
). Embolus slightly curved retrolaterally on distal half (
Fig. 32A, B
).

Colour pattern: In ethanol the colour is brown, with the opisthosoma, legs, and palps darker (
Fig. 31A
). In live specimens the colour is dark brown, with the femora slightly darker (
Fig. 1J
).
